      • pack

        public static java.util.ArrayList<ContainerPackingResult> pack(java.util.List<Container> containers,
                                                               java.util.List<Item> itemsToPack,
                                                               java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> algorithmTypeIDs)
        Given a series of AlgorithmIDs, this method will compute the solution to a box packing problem with each of them. As for the time of this writing, the only implemented algorithm for 3D bin packing is EB_AFIT, so this can be dismissed, and optionally deleted.
        Parameters:
        containers - The containers in which the items go.
        itemsToPack - The items to be packed.
        algorithmTypeIDs - The algorithm IDs.
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of ContainerPackingResult objects, one for each algorithm ID.
